  <div class="ct">
  
<p>I can tell you from my own experience and observations of newer teachers that it take 5 or 6 years to become pretty good at this. &nbsp;During this time period many teachers quit because the job is too hard or they find out it is not for them.</p>
<p>I also know that most teachers continue to learn and become better at their craft as the years go on. &nbsp;I am currently in my second year of my third master's program. &nbsp;I don't need the degree, but I am learning so much about teaching that didn't exist 30 years ago it is well worth it. &nbsp;</p>
<p>We need to make education a more competitive field, better pay and higher requirements for perspective teachers. &nbsp;Yes, there may be some bad teachers out there but we are driving off many good ones by cheapening education.</p>

