  <a href="/user/uid:107036">dizzydean</a>, <a href="/user/uid:99191">RosyFinch</a>, <a href="/user/uid:956537">allison88</a>, <a href="/user/uid:273307">pdxteacher</a>, <a href="/user/uid:47388">MHB</a>, <a href="/user/uid:220989">quill</a>, <a href="/user/uid:233186">The Lone Apple</a>, <a href="/user/uid:45368">historys mysteries</a>, <a href="/user/uid:17483">ssgbryan</a>, <a href="/user/uid:314189">joemac53</a>, <a href="/user/uid:3962">grollen</a>, <a href="/user/uid:13674">celdd</a>, <a href="/user/uid:15174">elfling</a>, <a href="/user/uid:302836">AverageJoe42</a>, <a href="/user/uid:198775">Grandma Susie</a>, <a href="/user/uid:157079">not this time</a>, <a href="/user/uid:71416">Naniboujou</a>, <a href="/user/uid:316545">IamGumby</a>, <a href="/user/uid:972826">jsb16</a>, <a href="/user/uid:259558">Free Jazz at High Noon</a>, <a href="/user/uid:233649">Mostel26</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>There are no "universally competent" employees in any profession. &nbsp;However, after teaching in five schools within two different states, I have had just two colleagues that I would deem as the older teacher who is unwilling to be a part of the team. &nbsp;</p>
<p>On the other hand, I have served as a mentor educator and have seen new teachers struggle for the first several years of teaching as they learn classroom management and other essential skills. &nbsp;I have also seen some with lots of enthusiasm, but little knowledge of their content area.</p>
<p>The education system relies on the seasoned teacher to provide the support for the schools, particularly with the plethora of MBA-type young administrators that are being hired. &nbsp;The ever-changing educational landscape requires the "wise vet teacher" to balance out the push for new "reforms."</p>
<p>Sometimes, it's best to not to engage in assumptions.</p>

  </div>
