<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:20253">bobtmn</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>I would never have made it otherwise. &nbsp;It just irritates me when it is implied that <em>all</em> long-term teachers are highly competent. &nbsp;That's the source of my pique. &nbsp; Because you're right--in <em>every</em> profession there are people who are crappy workers, or worn out, or irresponsible, or lazy. &nbsp;Yet it seems taboo to state that teachers are no exception.</p>
<p>I think people who have had their child stuck in a classroom for a year with one of those lousy teachers is going to be a lot more sensitive about that experience than the time they had to deal with the incompetent airline ticket agent or the hours-late repair guy. &nbsp;It is the rare student (and parent) who has not had to endure one of those lost education years. &nbsp;And that's infuriating. &nbsp;I would hope good teachers feel the same and would favor measures to reduce those bad apple numbers to as low as possible.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
