  <div class="ct">
  
<p>"Universal high-quality public education" has never existed in America.</p>
<p>Universal education for kids with disabilities was not mandated until the mid 1970s.</p>
<p>My classmates with last names that end in 'z' will tell you stories about having administrators change their schedules from calculus to woodshop.</p>
<p>Low income kids, kids of color, kids who lived in poor neighborhoods have never been guaranteed anything. The education they got was more a matter of luck than universal intent.</p>
<p>In the past, we educated fewer kids, and we cared less if they dropped out.</p>

