    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>So there's points 2, 3, and 4 right there.</p>
<p>I did teach in rural Montana, so I had nowhere near 150 students. The graduating class had less than 20 students, in fact. But I was required to attend <em>all</em> home sports events, rotating ticket and concession duties, as part of my contract. All school year long.</p>
<p>As a special bonus, there's not a hell of a lot of summer work in rural Montana for a teacher. And teaching isn't even considered a <em>real job.</em></p>
<p>From my experience, and the teachers I've worked with over the past 15 years, pdx is not describing an extremely unusual set of circumstances, no.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:41637">Daddy Bartholomew</a> on <a href="/comments/1234916/51230824#c281">Sun Sep 01, 2013 at 09:49:52 PM PDT</a></p>
