<p>I teach general music to every student in the school. &nbsp;Some students struggle as they have trouble hearing pitch. &nbsp;I still persist with them. I evaluate them in one way or another every time I see them as I use the information I glean to drive my instruction. &nbsp;This is why pacing guides are so bad. &nbsp;Some students need to move at a different pace through different parts of the curriculum.</p>
<p>As far as videotaping students performing goes--there would be no way for the third party to assess any value added. &nbsp;I have some kids that start out completely tone deaf. &nbsp;By the end of the school year, they are able to sing a limited range of pitches in tune and match pitch. &nbsp;This is a huge improvement. &nbsp;To record them singing, however would not show the improvement. &nbsp;I won't even go into the anxiety some kids experience at the thought of being recorded. &nbsp;Many of them don't perform well under those circumstances. &nbsp;</p>

