<p>No one considers that maybe every teacher, or maybe 90% of teachers in a particular school might be stars.</p>
<p>If you have a teacher not worthy of merit pay, you probably should be working on removing that teacher.</p>
<p>The reality is that merit pay in what is a cooperative team environment creates friction and tension, not excellence. Your 3rd grade teacher can't be excellent if your 2nd grade teacher isn't doing her job well.</p>
<p>I'll also note that I've not seen anyone advocate for 'merit pay' for firefighters, police officers, governors, or mayors, just as an example.</p>
<p>What teachers need aren't bonuses as much as they need to be paid enough to buy a house near in the community, to meet typical needs, and to send their kids to college.</p>

