<p>...wants to get rid of the bad teacher, he can.</p>
<p>It takes time, but the idea that "bad teachers" can't be fired is a myth.</p>
<p>(When evaluations are subjective, instead of based on standardized tests, even <strong>good</strong> teachers can be fired.)</p>
<p>The problem is that most Principals in poor neighborhoods have <em>no incentive to remove bad teachers</em>. The families are locked into the school, they cannot afford to flee to the suburbs and they have little or no political power. The families have no <strong>choice</strong> and they must take whatever horrible teacher the Principal inflicts upon them.</p>

