  <div class="ct">
  
<p>I'll drop in the unsolicited and off topic suggestion of an SF series that also loves math and mathematicians, the Liaden Universe by Sharon Lee and Steve Miller.</p>
<p>One of the books is currently free as an eBook:<br />
<a href="http://www.baenebooks.com/p-1026-fledgling.aspx">Fledgling</a></p>
<p>We meet Theo as a teenager, a bit clumsy, but good at her studies. She uses lacemaking to work out problems in math. She lives in a high surveillance world, and we see her first trying to make her way as a student when every misstep is watched by the authorities...</p>
<p>If you read the whole thing, you'll find out that the series is named for a character who was the premier mathematician of his day. :-) And nearly every hero in the novel series is quite good at math, because in this universe, it's a prerequisite for being a pilot.</p>

