<li id="c54">
  <div class="cx" id="cx51225901">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">Rank and yank</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1234916/51225901#c54?mode=alone;showrate=1#c54">17+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:15174">elfling</a>, <a href="/user/uid:62286">JanL</a>, <a href="/user/uid:71416">Naniboujou</a>, <a href="/user/uid:129942">rodentrancher</a>, <a href="/user/uid:56610">ladybug53</a>, <a href="/user/uid:233649">Mostel26</a>, <a href="/user/uid:257122">belinda ridgewood</a>, <a href="/user/uid:34438">Kidspeak</a>, <a href="/user/uid:71628">fiddler crabby</a>, <a href="/user/uid:956537">allison88</a>, <a href="/user/uid:10302">Caniac41</a>, <a href="/user/uid:107036">dizzydean</a>, <a href="/user/uid:154707">Dragon5616</a>, <a href="/user/uid:302836">AverageJoe42</a>, <a href="/user/uid:273307">pdxteacher</a>, <a href="/user/uid:972826">jsb16</a>, <a href="/user/uid:259558">Free Jazz at High Noon</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Someday the survivors will look back on this period and acknowledge US public education was virtually destroyed by misapplication of a faulty management strategy: the Six Sigma system developed at Motorola and used to devastating effect by Jack Welch at GE. In a nutshell, it "ranks and yanks" in order to pare payrolls to the bone.</p>
<p>Management develops a productivity metric like test scores (the metric is often entirely arbitrary, since metrics that can accurately assess both volume and quality are very difficult to devise, as Soviet central planning found out the hard way); this metric is then applied frequently to divide the workforce up into five "productivity" quintiles; those in the bottom quintile are then fired. The next time the metric is applied those falling into the new bottom quintile are usually those who'd fallen into the fourth quintile on the previous occasion; they too are fired. Keep doing this year after year until almost no one is left, then declare the enterprise to have "failed" and sell it off to Bain Capital (or, in the case of public education, turn everything &nbsp;over to the charter schools).</p>
<p>Jack Welch used this to eliminate hundreds of thousands of jobs at GE, and he was rewarded for it with one of the highest "golden parachute" packages in corporate history.<br />
&nbsp;</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:69809">LanceBoyle</a> on <a href="/comments/1234916/51225901#c54">Sun Sep 01, 2013 at 10:37:38 AM PDT</a></p>
  <p class="cl">
  
 
 
  
    
   

 
 
 </p> 
  </div>
  </div>
</li> 


	


