<li id="c61">
  <div class="cx" id="cx51225945">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">the 1% vision for "education"</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1234916/51225945#c61?mode=alone;showrate=1#c61">6+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:62286">JanL</a>, <a href="/user/uid:233649">Mostel26</a>, <a href="/user/uid:71628">fiddler crabby</a>, <a href="/user/uid:956537">allison88</a>, <a href="/user/uid:107036">dizzydean</a>, <a href="/user/uid:154707">Dragon5616</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Schools are warehouse like bldgs. The "classes" are on a screen at the front. There's no teacher, just a person in front who has the manual for the class who can answer some basic and general questions. The curriculum is whatever someone pays for it to be. Every student must purchase a copy of "Microsoft School" version whatever their grade. (Bill Gates has to have some reason to be involved in the movement) The halls have 1 armed guard for every 20 students.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig">
