<p>...to a "prevailing zeitgeist?" I'm curious.</p>
<p>Years ago, at my grandmother's funeral in Brooklyn, I was stunned to see my 2'nd grade nun arrive, assisted into the wake with younger nuns holding each arm, almost like she was floating toward me, like a ghost. She looked like she was 120 years old. I couldn't believe it when I saw her face for the first time in like 20 years and remembered her like I had just walked into 2'nd grade classroom. &nbsp;She greeted me by name, grasped my hand into her two milky white silky soft hands and kissed me, and said how much she'd loved my Grandmother. She proceeded to do the same to all of my siblings, by name, all of whom also had her for 2'nd grade.</p>
<p>I couldn't stop watching her. She moved on to my Aunt &nbsp;who apparently also had this nun for 2'nd grade and she did and said the same things.</p>
<p>She moved on down the line to my parents and I was astonished to see that they'd also had her for 2'nd grade! She said the same things and added a remark about how I'd grown up as if to congratulate my parents.</p>
<p>She went up to the casket and touched my grandmother's hands and prayed quietly for a few moments.</p>
<p>I still wonder to this day if my Grandmother had her for 2'nd grade...</p>
