<p>I do feel, by the way, that one of the main problems in terms of getting the public to understand this reality, is that most people do not perceive any special, unique, skill in teaching. Sure, there are factors like passion, patience, and persistence which are important. And organizational skills must also be important. But those are life skills important to everybody. So do uniquely professional skills related to teaching exist? I think most people would say "let me think about that one a while."</p>
<p>Yet, those are the skills that take 5 or six years to develop, and since the process is sink or swim for many (most?) teachers, a standard vocabulary to transmit and reflect upon them doesn't really exist. &nbsp;</p>
